1. Auto add crontab jobs

	Every time this scripts run it first checks the crontab -l command output and if */10 * * * * /path/to/the/script/SecurityAlert.sh entry is found is do nothing but if this entry is not found then it will create this entry

2. Make this script available for major linux distro like Ubuntu Fedora LinuxMint Redhat CentOS Debian & ArchLinux

	1. Identify Linux distro with the help of uname -a and grep commands

	2. Checks if twidge is installed on particular linux distro

	3. Where Other Linux distro stores the authentication failure message
